{
  "texts": [
    "Three types of empirical outcomes were reported in the studies (see Figure 4B).",
    "Most studies analysed the effects of saliency maps (i.e., benefits, costs, null effects) compared to a baseline without saliency maps (69.1%).",
    "Some studies analysed whether different saliency maps led to different outcomes (55.9%) and some analysed whether saliency maps were superior or inferior to extensions and combinations with other types of XAI (36.8%).",
    "The dependent variables used to analyse human task performance are summarised in Figure 4C.",
    "The majority of studies (77.9%) assessed participants' accuracy in solving the respective task."
  ]
}